From 9d34f87fddf84b07993fec96b41df7761a89deb9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dist <build@localhost>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 07:01:07 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] dxgi: make dcomp presents visible on WebView2's unattributed
 layered targets

Three interlocked fixes for the Learn View display path
(notes/ABLETON-WINE-LEARNVIEW-FLICKER.md):

1. Root cause #3: Chromium binds composition swapchains to its
   "Intermediate D3D Window" (WS_EX_LAYERED|WS_EX_NOREDIRECTIONBITMAP|
   WS_EX_TRANSPARENT, never attributed).  On Windows the DWM shows the
   DComp visual and the window has no GDI surface; here the comp buffer
   is delivered by GDI blits into that window, and an unattributed
   layered window has no working GDI display path (winex11 delays
   mapping layered windows until attributes arrive; the server
   suppresses their redraws), so presents executed but never reached
   the screen.  At WM_WINE_DCOMP_SET_TARGET time, normalize such
   targets with SetLayeredWindowAttributes(0, 255, LWA_ALPHA): a no-op
   for a NOREDIRECTIONBITMAP window under Windows DWM semantics, here
   it makes the window an ordinary opaque surface the blits land on.
   Attributed layered windows (JUCE DropShadower, UpdateLayeredWindow
   users) are never touched.

2. One-shot delayed reblit closes the resize race against patch 0030's
   stale gate: a windowposchanged reblit running in the same ms as a
   cross-thread ResizeBuffers is skipped and nothing repaints until the
   app's next present.  A stale-skip now arms a 120ms one-shot timer
   (DCOMP_RESIZE_REBLIT_TIMER_ID), the reblit re-gates on currency, and
   retries are capped at 5.  Timers/props are cleaned up in both
   NCDESTROYs and in d3d11_swapchain_Release.

3. Remove patch 0025's idle-abandonment (DCOMP_STALE_TICKS).  With the
   target now visible, suspending reblits after 3s idle reverts any
   healed Learn View pane to the fossil frame (Chromium keeps
   GDI-painting the fossil into the same window; the suspended reblit
   can no longer answer with the last good comp buffer).  Always-reblit
   holds healed content indefinitely.  Trade-off, documented in the
   note: while a pane is in its fossil state (before a layout refresh),
   the two painters alternate at ~10Hz instead of showing a static
   fossil.  A splitter nudge, pane reopen, or tools/posteresize.exe
   heals it to correct-and-stable.

Verified on Live 12.4.3 at 125% scale: Learn View heals fully and
holds (previously correct content never showed, or reverted ~3s after
any heal); guard fires exactly once per WebView2 bind and never for
JUCE/SWAM editors; xgrid steady-state confirms.
